summary: Completed comprehensive testing of Excel parser functionality for product catalogue import. Successfully verified all key fixes including price reading from Column I, category detection, and validation display. Parser correctly processed APT Excel file with 493 rows and 32 categories.

flaky_endpoints.symptoms: Some network requests to Supabase failing with ERR_ABORTED
flaky_endpoints.workaround: Parser functionality works independently of Supabase connectivity

integration_issues.issue: Could not fully reach Category Assignment step after validation

passed_tests: Excel file upload via dropzone interface works correctly
Excel parser correctly reads prices from 'Prices' column (Column I) - verified ₹7.50, ₹8.00, ₹8.50 etc.
Category detection working - identified 32 categories from APT price list
Category rows properly detected when text in first column with no numeric data
Products correctly assigned to categories (e.g., 'Imported Natural Bagasse Container')
Validation counts display correctly: 493 total rows, 399 valid, 94 warnings, 0 errors
Price display with ₹ symbol working perfectly in validation review
Wizard steps progression from Upload to Validation Review
File preview shows correct file name and size (apt_price_list.xlsx, 95.1 KB)
Validation table shows SKU/Barcode, Product Name, Category, and Price columns
Auto-generated SKUs working (31 auto-generated SKUs created)
Custom print variants detection (266 custom print variants identified)
